LIMITATIONS:

* Does not use real-time sensor data (simulation only)
* Considers only number of vehicles, not speed or road size
* No handling of emergency vehicles (ambulance, fire truck, etc.)
* Assumes traffic changes are uniform and predictable, which is not realistic
* Works for a single intersection only, not multiple connected signals
* Does not consider traffic rules or turning movements

Future scope:
* Integrate real-time traffic sensors or cameras to collect live vehicle data instead of using fixed values
* Add priority for emergency vehicles (ambulance, fire trucks) to improve response time
* Expand the system to handle multiple intersections with coordinated signals for better city-wide traffic management

target users:
* Traffic management authorities (to control and optimize traffic signals)
* City planners / smart city developers (for designing efficient road systems)
* Researchers and students (to study and improve traffic algorithms)
